🔥 Q6. Cyber Security Safeguards + Access Control + Audit + Authentication & Biometrics (12M)
Cyber Security Safeguards:
Cybersecurity safeguards are measures used to protect systems, networks, and data from attacks and unauthorized access.
Overview (Safeguards):
Firewalls
Antivirus software
Encryption
Access control
IDS/IPS
Backup & recovery
Security awareness

Access Control:
Access control restricts access to resources to authorized users only.
Types:
RBAC (Role-Based)
MAC (Mandatory)
DAC (Discretionary)
ABAC (Attribute-Based)
Importance: Prevents unauthorized access and protects data.

Audit:
Audit is the process of evaluating security policies and controls.
Types:
Internal audit
External audit
IT audit
Compliance audit
Importance:
Identifies vulnerabilities
Ensures compliance
Improves security

Authentication:
Authentication verifies user identity.
Steps:
Identification
Verification
Validation

Biometrics:
Biometric authentication uses physical traits.
Examples:
Fingerprint
Face recognition
Retina scan

Conclusion:
Cybersecurity safeguards ensure complete protection through layered security.






